  Two man types of IP addresses, IPv4 and IPv6
  IPV4 e.g 192.168.1.1   32 bit numerical labels written in decimal format, each octet can vary from 0-255. the first three octets are the network portions and the last octet is the host portion.
  IPv6 e.g. 2001:db8:0:1234:0:567:8:1  128 bit alpha numeric labels in hexadecimal format, and more efficient, each group can represent a value from 0000 to FFFF
  Private IP address usually starts with 192, used withing local network and not routable on the internet 
  Public IP address is assigned by internet service provider and is unique across internet allowign communication and routable on the internet
  Static IP addresses are fixed and do notchange over time, 
  Dynamic IP addresses are automatically assigned by a network when a device connects and can change over time and managed by the dynamic host configuration           protocol (DHCP) , more cost effective and effiecnt for isps.
